ill be more efficient than buffer.remove.", "author": "wuchong", "createdAt": "2020-06-04T13:16:48Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTI0Mzk0NA=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTMzMzEzOA==", "url": "https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/12303#discussion_r435333138", "bodyText": "@wuchong  I agree with you, but I think we also should subtract buffer.currentTopNum =  buffer.currentTopNum - 1 after remove lastElement, So is it appropriate to add a method in TopNBuffer such as public void minusTopNum(int delta) { currentTopNum -= delta; },\nwe should call this method behind dataState.put(lastKey, new ArrayList<>(lastList)), what do you think it?", "author": "lsyldliu", "createdAt": "2020-06-04T15:08:44Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTI0Mzk0NA=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTM0MDMyOA==", "url": "https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/12303#discussion_r435340328", "bodyText": "Good point. I just find that maybe we can use TopNBuffer#removeLast directly here.", "author": "wuchong", "createdAt": "2020-06-04T15:18:40Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTI0Mzk0NA=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTY1MjQ0NQ==", "url": "https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/12303#discussion_r435652445", "bodyText": "Good idea, I don't want to break the atomicity of TopNBuffer,  so I don't want to add new method which can operate currentTopNum directly in this class,  prefer to use TopNBuffer#removeLast", "author": "lsyldliu", "createdAt": "2020-06-05T02:10:29Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTI0Mzk0NA=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQzNTY1ODE3Ng==", "url": "https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/12303#discussion_r435658176", "bodyText": "But, I find TopNBuffer#removeLast also iterate the list, the efficient problem also exist.", "author": "lsyldliu", "createdAt": "2020-06-05T02:34:46Z", "replyToRevie